          SECTION 3.1 Hardware Components - The TYMNET Engine          ___________________________________________________


          The TYMNET Engine  is the  standard computer  used in  the cus-
          tomer's network.   It is a  high performance  micro-code driven
          processor with sixteen sets of sixteen registers.  The internal
          cycle time is 125 nanoseconds.  Each  register is 32 bits wide.
          The processor has 3 I/O interrupt levels plus system interrupts
          and can contain up to a megabyte of memory.

          The TYMNET Engine is designed for  high reliability and ease of
          maintenance.  Its  modular design allows  expedient replacement
          of  the sub-assembly  components, resulting  in minimum  repair
          time should a failure occur.   When proper configuration guide-
          lines are  followed, the  TYMNET Engine  will provide  the user
          with at least 98% system  availability, excluding exterior com-
          munication components and environmental conditioning.

          Operational diagnostics are fully  integrated with the software
          components which run in the TYMNET  Engine.  This allows detec-
          tion of problems  and provides data for easy  analysis prior to
          serious impact on user throughput or availability.

          A site documentation  package including  Engine schematic  dia-
          grams is provided at each installation site.

          Following are  descriptions of  the various  components of  the
          TYMNET  Engine.   Configuration  limitations  are  noted  where
          applicable.


