          SECTION 4.0 NETWORK CONTROL CENTER COMPONENTS          _____________________________________________


          The NCC  hardware configuration  consists of  a combination  of
          TYMNET Engines  in the  private network  with special  ISIS job
          slots, and limited support from NCC programs running on a Tyms-
          hare PDP-10 through a network gateway from TYMNET.

          The purpose  of the NCC system  is to provide a  monitoring and
          control facility for the customer's network.


          SECTION 4.1 Accounting          ______________________


          The accounting function of  the NCC consists of  a process run-
          ning on an ISIS node.

          The Raw Accounting  Merger (RAM) program runs in a  job slot on
          an ISIS node.  RAM collects accounting information from network
          Supervisor nodes,  sorts the information into  complete session
          records, and records them on magnetic tape.  For more detail on
          this program refer to the RAM User's Guide.                                    ________________


          SECTION 4.2 User Validation          ___________________________


          The user validation programs are used to  add a new user to the
          CUD or  to modify the  information concerning an  existing user
          entry in  the CUD.  The  ISIS Validation Program  (VAL) updates
          the CUD residing on a network  Supervisor node and copies these
          updates to  the MUDs for  the other network  Supervisors.  This
          program     is      described     in     detail      in     the
          ISIS_Validation_Program_(VAL)_User's_Guide.          ____ __________ _______ _____ ______ _____


          SECTION 4.3 Network Assembler and Debugger          __________________________________________


          The Network Assembler  and Debugger (NAD) is  a cross assembler
          used to assemble, load, and debug  network code running on TYM-
          NET  Engines.  Normally,  NAD is  used to  create binary  files
          which are then loaded by the LOADII program.

          NAD also  provides the  user with the  ability to  log in  to a
          debug module in  any network node.   The symbol table  is main-
          tained on  the NCC  host computer and  thus accessible  to NAD.
          Using the symbol table and the circuit to the network node, the
          user has  the ability to  perform online symbolic  debugging in
          any network node which runs on a TYMNET Engine.




