          SECTION 4.4 Downline Loader          ___________________________


          The program LOADII which  runs on the NCC can be  used to down-
          line load or upline  dump network nodes.  This  program is cur-
          rently only available on a TYMNET host computer.  The operation
          of  this program  is explained  in  more detail  in the  LOADII                                                                   ______
          User's_Guide.          ______ _____


          SECTION 4.5 Network Simulator (SIMNET)          ______________________________________


          SIMNET is a model of a TYMNET network which is designed to help
          the user configure  their network through optimal  placement of
          nodes and lines.  This program only runs  on a TYMNET host com-
          puter.  It  is used  mostly for  monitoring network  growth and
          planning for network expansion.  It is not a real-time model of
          the  network but  runs from  a session  file which  is used  to
          describe network  traffic.  Typically, this  session file  is a
          derivative of  the network  accounting information  produced by
          the Accounting Merger program on the NCC host computer.

          The Network Simulator gives you the  ability to make trial net-
          work configuration changes, try  them out with a  fully config-
          ured network, and then try taking  different links or nodes out
          of the network to determine what  would actually happen to net-
          work  traffic  if  that  event   really  occurred.   SIMNET  is
          described in more detail in supporting documentation.





















