          SECTION 5.0 AREAS OF REPONSIBILITY          __________________________________




          SECTION 5.1 Tymshare          ____________________


          It is the  responsibility of Tymshare to  perform the following
          tasks:

          o  Install hardware  and software systems  as described  in the
             Pilot Test Procedure.

          o  Install additional  hardware and software systems  which are
             ordered  by the  customer according  to  the guidelines  set
             forth in the delivery and installation agreement.

          o  Provide classes for  customer personnel as set  forth in the
             training procedures  agreement.  These classes  are intended
             to teach customer  personnel the  TYMNET software  architec-
             ture, the  hardware architecture of  the TYMNET  Engine, and
             the skills needed to maintain and operate a private network.

          o  Assist the  customer in  performing the  Pilot Test  and the
             Acceptance Tests.

          o  Make any changes necessary to systems  installed in the net-
             work so that these systems meet the Network Specifications.

          o  Tymshare will provide ongoing procedures that allow the cus-
             tomer to keep current on Tymshare hardware/software.

              (1) Distribution and installation of software releases.
              (2) Distribution and installation of software patches.
              (3) System generation procedures
              (4) Problem  reporting  procedures   for  hardware/software
                  problems.
              (5) A procedure for requesting software enhancements.
















